PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780974217
OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FThis comes amid the United States
OL,7,FNavy's decision to stop all oil
OL,8,Fimports from Central and South America.
OL,10,FThe American oil embargo has left the
OL,11,FCaribbean island in crisis, forcing
OL,12,Fthe local officials to choose which
OL,13,Fneighbourhoods to cut off and which to
OL,14,Fleave connected.
OL,16,FBlackouts in Cuba can last up to 24
OL,17,Fhours at a time, and only a fortunate
OL,18,Ffew have enough petrol to use their
OL,19,Fvehicles, reports ITV News US
OL,20,FCorrespondent Dan Rivers
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780974217
OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FOften, the outages last for more than
OL,7,F24 hours, putting life on hold for
OL,8,Fthose affected.
OL,10,FCuba has endured decades of sanctions
OL,11,Fand trade restrictions, but the
OL,12,Fchoking off of its oil supply, which
OL,13,Fcomes almost entirely from Venezuela
OL,14,Fand Mexico, has left the country on
OL,15,Fthe brink.
OL,17,FThe Trump administration wants to
OL,18,Fcoerce Cuba into accepting sweeping
OL,19,Freforms, making it more aligned with
OL,20,Fthe US and less aligned with countries
OL,21,Flike Russia.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780974217
OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FLast month, John Ratcliffe, the head
OL,7,Fof the CIA, held a summit with senior
OL,8,FCuban officials, delivering a stark
OL,9,Fmessage: Allow real change or face
OL,10,Fmilitary intervention.
OL,12,FDonald Trump said in March that he
OL,13,Fthinks he will have the "honour of
OL,14,Ftaking Cuba" and has repeated his
OL,15,Fthreats to topple the Communist
OL,16,Fgovernment with increasing regularity.
OL,18,FYet Cuba's president, Miguel Diaz-
OL,19,FCanel, remains intransigent - and
OL,20,Fordinary Cubans are paying the price.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780974217
OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FPetrol is rationed to 20 litres a
OL,7,Fmonth per person, but on the black
OL,8,Fmarket, if they can find it, Cubans
OL,9,Fare paying more than #5 a litre for
OL,10,Fpetrol.
OL,12,FIt means many of the classic 1950s
OL,13,Fvehicles, which have become a
OL,14,Ftrademark of the tourist industry, lie
OL,15,Fstranded.
OL,17,FThose still operating are charging
OL,18,Feven higher prices for the dwindling
OL,19,Fnumber of tourists wandering around
OL,20,FHavana's historic streets.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
