OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FThis week, we watched as international
OL,7,Fhotel chains were forced to change
OL,8,Ftheir names to avoid incurring US
OL,9,Fsecondary sanctions.
OL,11,FMastercard and Visa have stopped
OL,12,Fworking here, and the currency is
OL,13,Fbecoming more worthless against the US
OL,14,Fdollar - the preferred currency for
OL,15,Fbusinesses.
OL,17,FWhat was once a popular tourist
OL,18,Fdestination is now largely deserted.
OL,19,FCafes are empty, and bands play
OL,20,Frenditions of the Buena Vista Social
OL,21,FClub hits to empty terraces.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780974217
OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FTowers of rubbish are left rotting on
OL,7,Fmany street corners, some picked over
OL,8,Fby scavengers hoping to find a morsel
OL,9,Fof food or something worth salvaging.
OL,11,FIn a country where the health service
OL,12,Fwas once the apple of its eye, the
OL,13,Fsystem is now creaking under the
OL,14,Fpressure of the American blockade.
OL,16,FThere is a flourishing black market in
OL,17,Fmedicines advertised brazenly online
OL,18,Fby medical workers selling what they
OL,19,Fcan steal from hospitals.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
