OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FOne diplomatic source we spoke to
OL,7,Fthinks American military intervention
OL,8,Fis neither imminent nor inevitable,
OL,9,Fbut at the same time believes the US
OL,10,Fwill insist on change and is prepared
OL,11,Fto launch military action to achieve
OL,12,Fit.
OL,14,FFor its part, the Cuban government and
OL,15,Fits vastly inferior military have
OL,16,Fdistributed thousands of AK-47s to
OL,17,Fmembers of the Communist party, a
OL,18,Ftoken measure aimed at defence against
OL,19,Fa potential American invasion.
OL,21,FWould the US put boots on the ground?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780974217
OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FIt's still haunted by its failed
OL,7,Fmission at the Bay of Pigs in 1961
OL,8,Fwhen John F. Kennedy's attempt to
OL,9,Fdefeat Fidel Castro's men ended in
OL,10,Fhumiliation for the Americans.
OL,12,FCould the US, buoyed by its success in
OL,13,Fabducting Venezuelan President Nicolas
OL,14,FMaduro, attempt to snatch and put on
OL,15,Ftrial Castro's brother, 95-year-old
OL,16,FRaul, who was recently indicted by the
OL,17,FUS?
OL,19,FTrump may opt for a campaign of
OL,20,Fairstrikes to decapitate the regime,
OL,21,Fstarting with its current president.
OL,26,@uD@erpxD@Crz
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
